
*** HOW TO INSTALL & USE AMY2

(JL ALbarral, 3/3/2017)

> INTRODUCTION

amy2 is a program that allows users to control amy through CLI.

usage: amy2 <action> [<value>]

The available actions are:
	hs		move horizontal shoulder joint (degrees)
	vs		move vertical shoulder joint (degrees)
	elb		move elbow joint (degrees)
	hwri	move horizontal wrist joint (degrees)
	vwri	move vertical wrist joint (degrees)
	pan		move pan (degrees)
	tilt	move tilt (degrees)
	rad		move radius (cm)
	keep	keep tilt position (1 or 0)
	vpan	move pan at given speed (degrees/s)
	vtilt	move tilt at given speed (degrees/s)
	vrad	move radius at given speed (cm/s)
	stop	stop arm
	end		end amy




> INSTALLATION


1. Download amy

git clone https://github.com/albarral/amy.git


2. Build amy_main & amy_console projects (in Netbeans)


3. Make amy libs loadable globally:

(*)
touch amy.conf
echo /path_to_amy/amy_coms/dist/Debug/GNU-Linux
echo /path_to_amy/amy_utils/dist/Debug/GNU-Linux
sudo mv amy.conf /etc/ld.so.conf.d
sudo /sbin/ldconfig


4. Put config files in user's home folder:

(*)
cd 
mkdir .amy
cp /path_to_amy/logging/*.xml .amy


5. Create link to amy2 in user's home folder:

(*)
cd
ln -s /path_to_amy/amy_console/dist/Debug/GNU-Linux/amy2 amy2




(*) note: change path_to_amy for the amy installation path


